This place is small, and it can get crowded, but the fast moving employees keep the lines down and the customers happy. Most people grab-and-go, so it's not hard to find a spot to sit and munch.  The bagels are well made, though I wouldn't say they are necessarily delicious (the dough could prob use a bit more salt and likely some more premium ingredients in order to make them great), but they make for a perfectly serviceable NY bagel.  Bonus points for friendliness, and their policy of not charging extra for tofu cream cheese.

3.5 Stars but I'm rounding up.  When I moved to the neighborhood this place felt like a big step down from the Bagel Store in Williamsburg.  They're not the absolute best NY bagels.  But they've grown on me over the years and I enjoy the atmosphere--great cross-section of the neighborhood in and out weekend mornings.  The whole-wheat everything bagels are great.  The sandwiches are generally good (there are a lot of places in the neighborhood that don't serve bacon).  Service can sometimes leave a little to be desired, but generally friendly and fast.  Coffee is sub-par.
